&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Job Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The Ecosystem Success team at Parity focuses on supporting external development teams building solutions with and for the Substrate and Polkadot ecosystems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Substrate is a blockchain-building framework that makes it easy to create a custom blockchain optimized for any use case. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Substrate blockchains are natively compatible with Polkadot, a Level-0 blockchain solution that enables diverse blockchains &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;to interoperate seamlessly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The overall objective of the Ecosystem Success team is to improve both platforms, increase engineering capabilities and accelerate adoption of both Substrate and Polkadot. Therefore, in this role you will work hand in hand with the different engineering and business teams in the Substrate ecosystem, gathering feedback and sharing technical insights to inspire and inform the best developer groups worldwide about the potential of building cutting-edge blockchains with Substrate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The Substrate Builders Program Manager plays a vital role in our company, as well as in the Substrate and Polkadot Ecosystems. You will work in close contact with critical teams in the ecosystem to help them develop bleeding-edge blockchain projects. We are looking for a talented individual with the right mix of entrepreneurial instinct, technical and blockchain knowledge, and project management skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
